This paper deals with security issues in honeynets, which are commonly used in computer security research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses network infrastructure and communication protocols, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses software engineering and system design, which could place it in cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of virtual machines, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
